pageContext.claim: “Labor force participation rose 63.2 -- and rose to 63.2. That's a great number.”
pageContext.analysis: The labor force participation rate did rise to 63.2 percent but it was higher in 2013 -- and is still far below the level of 66 percent reached before the Great Recession. The retirement of the Baby Boom generation is an important factor in the decline in the labor force participation rate but Trump is took quick to say this is "a great number." The rate for the 25-54 age group is also still below the pre-Recession level.
